d Grenzen eines gesellschaftlich ambitionierten Beamtendichters beschreiben. Literatursoziologische, netzwerktheoretische und biographietheoretische Ansätze werden verbunden, um Richard Schaukal im Kontext der Moderne neu zu verorten.  aRichard Schaukal was in contact with some of literary modernism's most important protagonists. In his early creative years, he stylized himself as an independent, isolated poet. After World War I, Schaukal became increasingly visible as a cultural critic, using his letters, essays, and literary works to take a stand against the new realities. His biography offers insights into the aesthetic, social, and political developments of his time.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by FWF  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aModernism (Literature). 4aLiterarische Netzwerke. 4aLiteratur der Jahrhundertwende. 4aRichard Schaukal. 4aWiener Moderne. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aRichard Schaukal.  aViennese modernism.  aliterary networks.  aturn-of-the-century literature.2 aFWFefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831106182350 cprintz978311061801340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110619744zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110619744zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/97831106